708924f-a.title: Manhattan: 5th Avenue - 50th Street
708924f-a.text:
In a New Setting: St. Patricks Cathedral-- A new view of New Yorke
greatest completed sacred edifice, St. Patrick's (R.C.) Cathedral
on the east side of Fifth Ave. between 50th and 5lst Sts. Note the
new store building in right foreground, just being completed and
sOon to be occupied by Saks \& Co. Thts formerly was the site of the
Democratic Club.
Jan. 12, 1924  Underwood \&: Underwood.
Said to be the most imposing Church edifice in the U.S. The spires
rise to a height of 339 feet, and the building extends back 332 feet
on the side streets. The Cathedral was begun in 1858 and dedicated
21 years later.
